definition.value: A dietary fat supplement composed primarily of fish oil.
Fish oil supplementation has been used in function medicine to reduce cardiovascular disease risk and reduce inflammation.
A dietary fat supplement composed primarily of flaxseed oil.
Flaxseed oil supplementation has been used in function medicine for a variety of ailments including gastrointestinal complaints and cardiovascular disease.
A botanical dietary supplement composed primarily of a Ginkgo biloba plant leaf extract.
Ginkgo biloba supplementation has been used in functional medicine for a variety of ailments including peripheral artery disease and dementia.
A botanical dietary supplement composed primarily of the root or root extract of the Panax ginseng plant.
Ginseng supplementation has been used in functional medicine to stimulate immune function, improve well-being, and a variety of other health problems.
A dietary supplement composed primarily of the amino sugar glucosamine.
Glucosamine supplementation has been used in functional medicine for arthritis and pain.
A dietary supplement composed primarily of the hormone melatonin.
Melatonin supplementation has been used in functional medicine for circadian rhythm disruption and insomnia.
A botanical dietary supplement composed primarily of extract from the seeds of the Silybum marianum plant.
Milk thistle supplementation has been used in functional medicine for a variety of ailments including hepatitis, cirrhosis, and diabetes.
A dietary fat supplement composed primarily of omega-3 fatty acids eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA) and docosahexaenoic acid (DHA).
Omega-3- fatty acid supplementation has been used in function medicine for a variety of ailments including hypertriglyceridemia and rheumatoid arthritis.
A botanical dietary supplement composed primarily of red yeast rice (rice fermented with the mold Monascus purpureus).
Red yeast rice supplementation has been used in functional medicine to aid in digestion and reduce blood cholesterol.
A botanical dietary supplement composed primarily of resveratrol.
Resveratrol supplementation has been used in functional medicine to reduce blood pressure and improve cognition.
A botanical dietary supplement composed primarily of an extract of the flower of the Hypericum perforatum plant.

St. john's wort supplementation has been used in functional medicine for a variety of ailments including insomnia and depression. St. John's wort is a cytochrome P450 inducer and has known interactions with some medications.
A food object quality which describes the stability and completeness of the packaging material.
A food packaging integrity quality in which the packaging is undamaged and in the original form.
A food packaging integrity quality in which the packaging has been disturbed or is not in the original form.
A food packaging integrity quality which is compromised and has been opened by the consumer.
A food product which does not have any packaging or where packaging is removed.
A food packaging type which is intended for the consumer to remove or open to access food material.
This packaging type can be obtained by a consumer, without being re-packaged.
A food packaging type which is used in bulk food packaging and is removed prior to retail distribution.
A food product which lacks packaging.
A food product which lacks packaging and is not intended to be packaged.
A wafer which is rolled out thinly and baked before shaped into a hollow cylinder or a cone.
A shortbread cookie which originated in Spain and is very soft, crumbly, and contains nuts.
A type of barquillo which is filled with pulburon, common in the Philippines.

A snack food which is made from puffed rice with spices and chutneys.
A snack food which is made from moth bean flour, gram flour and spices and is popular in India.
A multi-component rice dish which consists of highly seasoned rice, spices, and vegetables, originating from the Indian subcontinent.
The dish is popular in India and may include meat in addition to the spiced rice and vegetables.
A salami which is primarily made with only pork meat and originated in the Calabria area of Italy.
This salami is traditionally made with pork, however over time has grown to occasionally include other meats too.
A patty which is made of spiced ground mutton lamb, beef or chicken, popular in Pakistan.
This is a Pashtun-style minced kebab, which is a popular street food in Pakistan and Afghanistan.
A chicken meat food product which consists of chicken wrapped around garlic butter and coated with breadcrumbs.
A bakery food product which usually contains a filling which is topped with a batter, biscuit or dumpling before being baked.
A bakery food product which usually contains stewed fruit and which is topped with a crumbly mixture of fat, flour and sugar.
A snack food which is based on deep fried dough with various fillings or flavourants that originated in South Asia.
A chaat which is made of vadas (fried flour balls) which are dipped in yogurt.
A hard biscuit which contains egg products, is square and has upturned corners.
Egg cracklets are a common in the Philippines and are consideered a type of biscuit.
A snack food which contains tinted sago that puffs up when deep friend and is known for being very colourful.
This dish is commonly made with potato starch, however potato free varieties do exist.
A stew which originates from the Indian subcontinent and is made of crushed or blended meat, lentils and spices and cooked to a thick paste.
A stew which consists of cubes of meat, lentils and spices which are slowly cooked to a thick paste.
Khichra is the meat based variant of rice dish from the Indian subcontinent called Khichdi. It is popular in India and Pakistan where it is sold as street food.
A prepared food product which primarily consists of rice with creole and cajun spices, meat, seafood and/or vegetables.
A spice mixture which consists of ground coriander seed, celery seed, basil, dill, parsley, blue fenugreek, summer savory, bay, leaf, mint and marigold.
Originates in Georgia and is a common ingredient of traditional Georgian dishes and sauces, such as kharcho.
A frozen dairy dessert which is unchurned and is similar to ice cream.
Originates in the Indian subcontinent.
A plant leaf food product which is harvested just after the cotyledon leaves developed with one set of true leaves.
A microgreen food product which is the whole product or a processed part.
A microgreen food product which includes the leaf only.
A microgreen food product which includes the stem only.
A microgreen food product which consists of more than one individual.
A semisoft cheese product which is traitionally made in the Brazilian state of Minas Gerais.
A multi-component food product which consists of cooked rice and vegetables, seafood or meat rolled in gim and served in bite size pieces.
Originated in Korea and is similar to sushi.
A food product which has been processed by a crumbling technique to break the food into smaller pieces.
A pudding which is made by boiling milk, sugar or jaggery, and most commonly rice, although this can be substitued for a different grain.

This dish is popular in the Indian subcontinent typically flavoured with desiccated coconut, cardamom, raisins, saffron, cashews, pistachios, almonds, or other dry fruits and nuts. Instead of rice kheer can be made with daals, bulgur wheat, millet, tapioca, vermicelli, or sweet corn.
A sauce which is composed of huacatay and other ingredients such as queso fresco, chilis and milk.
